verses.roman:
aiche amṛta-anna kṛṣṇe kara samarpaṇa
tomāra bhāgyera sīmā ke kare varṇana?"

synonyms: aiche—such; amṛta-anna—nectarean rice; kṛṣṇe—unto Lord Kṛṣṇa; kara samarpaṇa—you offer; tomāra—your; bhāgyera—of fortune; sīmā—limit; ke—who; kare varṇana—can describe.
translation: "You offer such nectarean rice to Kṛṣṇa. Who can estimate the limit of your fortune?"
